			<h2>
                Nicki Abel
            </h2>
            <p> 
                RGN, BSc (Hons), MSCN  <br />
                MS NEED Steering Committee and Syllabus Committee  
            </p>
            <br />

		    <p>
                Nicki Abel is a Lecturer Practitioner in MS at Birmingham City University and Queen Elizabeth 
                Hospital, Birmingham, UK working both in education as a Senior Lecturer in MS and clinical practice 
                as a Specialist MS Nurse. 
            </p>
            <p>
                She enjoys her dual role as she is passionate about both patient care and education. She organises 
                and manages bachelor level MS modules and also leads on other modules that educate on long term 
                conditions. Her latest achievement is the evolvement of an ‘online’ Bachelor of Science (BSc) educational 
                programme on specialist practice for those preferring an e-learning approach to education.  
            </p>
            <p>
                Nicki has a strong interest in sexuality issues and has written a booklet focusing on the sexuality 
                issues faced by women with MS which won an award from the British Medical Association. She is currently 
                carrying out a national research project on the effectiveness of fatigue management groups. 
            </p>
            <p>
                She obtained her bachelor of science in nursing degree at the University of Central England. She is 
                certified by the Multiple Sclerosis Nursing International Certification Board. She has authored several 
                articles on multiple sclerosis and is on the editorial board of MS in Focus. She is an immediate past 
                member of the Multiple Sclerosis International Certification Board (MSICB) and currently on the board 
                of the International Organisation of MS Nurses (IOMSN).
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>Disclosures</b>
                <br />
                Nicki Abel has nothing to disclose
            </p>
